1110
00:56:40,562 --> 00:56:42,530
<i>You could see it
in Frost's face.</i>

1111
00:56:42,597 --> 00:56:44,792
<i>If he didn't know
the caliber of the man</i>

1112
00:56:44,866 --> 00:56:46,994
that he was up against
before the interview started,

1113
00:56:47,069 --> 00:56:49,559
<i>he certainly knew
it halfway through
the President's first answer.</i>

1114
00:56:49,637 --> 00:56:52,504
NIXON: You see,
since the best advice is

1115
00:56:52,574 --> 00:56:56,169
almost always
of the confidential variety,

1116
00:56:56,244 --> 00:56:58,405
now the tapes have
been made public,

1117
00:56:58,480 --> 00:57:00,971
people are unlikely
ever to feel comfortable

1118
00:57:01,049 --> 00:57:03,609
<i>speaking in confidence
at the White House.</i>

1119
00:57:03,685 --> 00:57:07,519
<i>They're less likely
to offer that advice.
So in the end,</i>

1120
00:57:07,589 --> 00:57:09,820
<i>it's the whole
political system and,</i>

1121
00:57:09,892 --> 00:57:12,826
<i>by implication, it's
