1138
00:58:02,111 --> 00:58:03,100
<i>We have to move this along.</i>

1139
00:58:03,179 --> 00:58:04,874
<i>This is desperate, John.
Do something.</i>

1140
00:58:04,947 --> 00:58:07,347
Twenty-three minutes
on one question?

1141
00:58:07,416 --> 00:58:08,474
<i>Okay, let's take a break.</i>

1142
00:58:08,551 --> 00:58:09,916
<i>Let's change the tapes.
Come on, man.</i>

1143
00:58:09,985 --> 00:58:11,179
<i>Stop tape.</i>

1144
00:58:12,755 --> 00:58:14,017
<i>DIRECTOR:
I'm sorry, gentlemen.</i>

1145
00:58:14,089 --> 00:58:15,750
<i>We have to take a break.
Tape change.</i>

1146
00:58:15,825 --> 00:58:18,623
<i>Oh. Okay, how's that?
You getting what you need?</i>

1147
00:58:18,694 --> 00:58:19,956
<i>It's fantastic.</i>

1148
00:58:20,029 --> 00:58:21,621
<i>Good. Good. Thank you.</i>

1149
00:58:23,199 --> 00:58:24,359
<i>Excuse me. One moment, sir.</i>

1150
00:58:24,433 --> 00:58:26,526
<i>NIXON: Yeah, sure.
Take your time.</i>

1151
00:58:26,902 --> 00:58:28,870
<i>What are you doing, David?
You've got to
stop him rambling.</i>

1152
00:58:28,938 --> 00:58:31,133
<i>It's all right.
These are just
introductory exchanges.</i>

1153
00:58:31,207 --> 00:58:32,674
<i>But this session
only lasts two hours.</i>

1154
00:58:32,741 --> 00:58:35,437
<i>Nearly half of it's gone,
and we're wasting
valuable material, okay?</i>

1155
00:58:35,511 --> 00:58:37,775
The moment that he made
the decision to resign,

1156
00:58:37,847 --> 00:58:39,144
<i>we should be scoring
points with that stuff.</i>

1157
00:58:39,215 --> 00:58:40,375
Want me to switch to Vietnam?

1158
00:58:40,449 --> 00:58:41,938
<i>No. No.
We've got to
get something</i>

1159
00:58:42,016 --> 00:58:43,747
<i>out of that
resignation night.
All right?</i>

1160
00:58:43,820 --> 00:58:47,381
<i>That was Nixon at
his lowest point,
a total wreck. On his knees?</i>

1161
00:58:47,457 --> 00:58:49,948
<i>Praying with Kissinger?
Come on, you can nail
him with that stuff.</i>

1162
00:58:50,026 --> 00:58:51,391
Listen, was that okay?

1163
00:58:51,461 --> 00:58:52,758
<i>Perfect, sir.</i>

1164
00:58:52,829 --> 00:58:55,491
<i>It didn't sound too
arrogant or self-serving?</i>

1165
00:58:55,565 --> 00:58:59,057
<i>Not at all.
You sounded controlled,
even-handed, statesmanlike.</i>

1166
00:58:59,135 --> 00:59:00,329
<i>Good.</i>

1167
00:59:00,403 --> 00:59:01,563
<i>Now continue
exactly the same way.</i>

1168
00:59:01,638 --> 00:59:03,538
<i>Long answers.
Control the space.</i>

1169
00:59:03,607 --> 00:59:04,595
<i>Don't let him in.</i>

1170
00:59:04,673 --> 00:59:05,935
<i>Okay, got you.</i>

1171
00:59:09,179 --> 00:59:11,204
<i>DAVIS: Set. And roll.</i>

1172
00:59:16,052 --> 00:59:21,115
<i>We're coming
back on camera three
in four, three, two and...</i>

1173
00:59:23,560 --> 00:59:27,620
Reading the account
of those extraordinary
final days,

1174
00:59:27,696 --> 00:59:30,164
it seems your most
emotional moment came

1175
00:59:30,233 --> 00:59:33,566
<i>in that
heart-to-heart you had
with Henry Kissinger.</i>

1176
00:59:33,637 --> 00:59:37,266
Was that perhaps
the most emotional moment
of your career?

1177
00:59:37,741 --> 00:59:39,333
<i>RESTON: Good, good.
NIXON: Yes.</i>

1178
00:59:40,076 --> 00:59:45,378
<i>I would say it was
about as emotional
a moment as I've ever had.</i>

1179
00:59:47,551 --> 00:59:49,677
<i>Except, well,
you know,
it's hard to say</i>

1180
00:59:49,752 --> 00:59:51,846
what is the most
emotional moment,

1181
00:59:51,922 --> 00:59:54,517
<i>because each is different.</i>

1182
00:59:54,959 --> 00:59:58,053
<i>I remember the day
Eisenhower died.</i>

1183
00:59:58,129 --> 00:59:59,426
<i>For God's sake.</i>

1184
00:59:59,497 --> 01:00:03,763
<i>And the day I walked
my eldest daughter
Tricia down the aisle.</i>

1185
01:00:03,834 --> 01:00:06,530
And the day during
the impeachment hearings

1186
01:00:06,604 --> 01:00:10,233
<i>when Julie,
that's my youngest,
she came into my office,</i>

1187
01:00:10,308 --> 01:00:14,801
<i>she threw her arms around me,
she kissed me.
She cried, you know?</i>

1188
01:00:14,878 --> 01:00:17,780
<i>And she so seldom cries.</i>

1189
01:00:17,982 --> 01:00:20,314
<i>She said, "Daddy, you're
the finest man I know."</i>

1190
01:00:20,384 --> 01:00:22,375
<i>"Daddy, you're
the finest man I know"?</i>

1191
01:00:22,853 --> 01:00:26,345
<i>"And whatever you do,
I will support you.</i>

1192
01:00:27,425 --> 01:00:31,759
<i>"You just gotta
go through the fire,
you know, a little longer."</i>

1193
01:00:34,131 --> 01:00:35,893
<i>This is beautiful.</i>

1194
01:00:35,966 --> 01:00:39,129
So Kissinger and I were
in the Lincoln Sitting Room,

1195
01:00:39,202 --> 01:00:42,195
and together we began
to reminisce

1196
01:00:42,273 --> 01:00:46,107
<i>about some of
the great decisions that
we'd participated in.</i>

1197
01:00:46,177 --> 01:00:49,374
There was China,
the Soviet Union,

1198
01:00:49,447 --> 01:00:51,972
<i>the peace settlement
in Vietnam.</i>

1199
01:00:52,049 --> 01:00:56,076
<i>Now, let me
tell you something that
I never told anybody.</i>

1200
01:00:56,153 --> 01:01:00,590
<i>Whenever I have had
a really tough
decision to make...</i>

1201
01:01:00,925 --> 01:01:03,689
<i>Now, we were in
the Lincoln Sitting Room
at that time.</i>

1202
01:01:03,761 --> 01:01:07,459
<i>I have come into this room
for the purpose of praying.</i>

1203
01:01:08,500 --> 01:01:12,368
<i>"Now, Henry,
I'm a Quaker.
You're a Jew.</i>

1204
01:01:12,437 --> 01:01:14,405
<i>"Neither of us is
particularly orthodox,</i>

1205
01:01:14,473 --> 01:01:17,499
<i>"but I'd like to think
that each of us
in our own way</i>

1206
01:01:17,576 --> 01:01:20,567
<i>"has a deep
religious sensitivity.</i>

1207
01:01:20,645 --> 01:01:25,742
<i>"So if you don't mind,
could we just have a moment
of silent prayer?"</i>

1208
01:01:25,816 --> 01:01:30,049
<i>So we knelt down.
Now, this was in front
of that table where</i>

1209
01:01:30,122 --> 01:01:34,286
<i>Lincoln signed
the Emancipation
Proclamation.</i>

1210
01:01:34,359 --> 01:01:37,795
<i>And then after a few moments,
we both got up again,
and Henry says...</i>

1211
01:01:37,896 --> 01:01:39,454
<i>Is there... I'm sorry.</i>

1212
01:01:39,598 --> 01:01:40,758
Is there a problem?

1213
01:01:40,832 --> 01:01:41,856
<i>That's time.</i>

1214
01:01:42,434 --> 01:01:44,560
<i>We're over two hours.</i>

1215
01:01:44,635 --> 01:01:46,728
Really? So soon?

1216
01:01:47,438 --> 01:01:50,407
<i>Well, Mr. President,
I gather our time is up.</i>

1217
01:01:50,608 --> 01:01:52,406
<i>Gee, now, that's a pity.</i>

1218
01:01:52,477 --> 01:01:54,968
<i>You know,
I was beginning
to enjoy that.</i>

1219
01:01:58,950 --> 01:02:01,316
<i>That was terrific,
both of you.</i>

1220
01:02:01,386 --> 01:02:02,751
<i>We're getting some
great material.</i>

1221
01:02:02,821 --> 01:02:04,186
<i>You know,
it's so funny, too,</i>

1222
01:02:04,256 --> 01:02:07,691
<i>because I was expecting
questions on Vietnam.</i>

1223
01:02:07,758 --> 01:02:10,250
<i>And we prepared for that,
hadn't we, Jack?</i>

1224
01:02:10,328 --> 01:02:11,727
<i>Yes, so did I.</i>

1225
01:02:11,797 --> 01:02:14,925
<i>I guess we
just got caught up,
you know, reminiscing.</i>

1226
01:02:15,000 --> 01:02:16,025
<i>Indeed.</i>

1227
01:02:16,102 --> 01:02:18,366
So, day after tomorrow,
10:00, right?

1228
01:02:18,438 --> 01:02:19,530
<i>Yes, indeed.</i>

1229
01:02:19,605 --> 01:02:21,300
<i>I look forward to it.
Bye-bye.</i>

1230
01:02:28,780 --> 01:02:30,839
<i>There's no need
to say anything.</i>

1231
01:02:37,422 --> 01:02:39,550
<i>REPORTER 1 : Mr. President!
REPORTER 2: Mr. President!</i>

1232
01:02:39,792 --> 01:02:41,760
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

1233
01:02:42,628 --> 01:02:43,890
<i>REPORTER 3: Mr. President!</i>

1234
01:02:43,963 --> 01:02:45,294
<i>REPORTER 4:
Mr. President, please!</i>

1235
01:02:46,299 --> 01:02:47,527
(WHISPERING)
