the post-mortem for now?

1244
01:03:02,982 --> 01:03:05,041
<i>I don't mean to minimize it.
It's just I've got to
get back to LA</i>

1245
01:03:05,118 --> 01:03:06,517
<i>to meet some people
from Weed Eater.</i>

1246
01:03:06,586 --> 01:03:08,417
Thanks, everyone!
Great work!

1247
01:03:08,488 --> 01:03:10,683
<i>Marv, Lloyd, great day.
Bye, David.</i>

1248
01:03:10,757 --> 01:03:13,623
<i>I'll see you soon.
God bless!</i>

1249
01:03:16,661 --> 01:03:19,062
What the hell
is Weed Eater?

1250
01:03:19,365 --> 01:03:21,595
<i>It's a horticultural
mechanism.</i>

1251
01:03:21,667 --> 01:03:22,691
<i>One of our sponsors.</i>

1252
01:03:22,769 --> 01:03:24,134
What happened to Xerox?

1253
01:03:24,203 --> 01:03:26,468
What about
General Motors
or IBM?

1254
01:03:26,540 --> 01:03:29,600
<i>I gather that not all of
the blue-chip accounts
came through.</i>

1255
01:03:29,676 --> 01:03:31,871
<i>We do have Alpo.</i>

1256
01:03:31,945 --> 01:03:33,344
Dog food?

1257
01:03:33,413 --> 01:03:35,779
<i>(STUTTERING) Wait, John.
We're already taping.</i>

1258
01:03:36,282 --> 01:03:37,977
<i>So we're close, right?
We're very close?</i>

1259
01:03:38,050 --> 01:03:39,483
<i>That's probably a question
you should ask David.</i>

1260
01:03:39,552 --> 01:03:41,417
Are we close, John?

1261
01:03:44,323 --> 01:03:46,416
<i>I believe we're at 30%.</i>

1262
01:03:47,193 --> 01:03:48,683
To go? Or 30% sold?

1263
01:03:48,761 --> 01:03:51,458
<i>Again, that's probably
a question you should...</i>

1264
01:03:52,533 --> 01:03:54,125
<i>Sold, 30% sold.</i>

1265
01:03:54,835 --> 01:03:56,359
<i>Jesus...</i>

1266
01:03:56,503 --> 01:03:58,061
<i>I thought
we were practically
fully financed.</i>

1267
01:03:58,138 --> 01:04:01,265
<i>We were. But the financing
was always conditional
on advertising sales,</i>

1268
01:04:01,340 --> 01:04:03,035
<i>and no one predicted
that they'd fall apart
like this.</i>

1269
01:04:03,109 --> 01:04:05,009
Well, why have
they fallen apart?
Based on what?

1270
01:04:05,077 --> 01:04:07,875
<i>Credibility of the project.
What else are advertising
sales based on?</i>

1271
01:04:07,947 --> 01:04:10,108
<i>Listen,
I understand your concern.</i>

1272
01:04:10,183 --> 01:04:13,381
But could I ask you
to go a little easier on David
over the next couple of days,

1273
01:04:13,453 --> 01:04:15,921
<i>bearing in mind
the extraordinary pressure
that he's under?</i>

1274
01:04:15,989 --> 01:04:19,481
<i>'Cause at the moment,
he's effectively paying
for all this himself.</i>

1275
01:04:19,560 --> 01:04:23,222
<i>So he's in it
for a lot more than
just his reputation.</i>

1276
01:04:23,563 --> 01:04:24,860
<i>And we're not?</i>

1277
01:04:31,939 --> 01:04:35,534
<i>FROST: You seemed
very confident last time.</i>

1278
01:04:35,609 --> 01:04:38,545
<i>I don't understand.
