change of heart?</i>

1279
01:04:38,613 --> 01:04:41,173
<i>All right,
this is just madness.
It's Richard Nixon.</i>

1280
01:04:41,249 --> 01:04:45,480
<i>These interviews
will do mid-30s
audience share, minimum.</i>

1281
01:04:45,552 --> 01:04:52,185
<i>Jimmy! Yes.
Yes, back again, like
the proverbial bad penny.</i>

1282
01:04:52,259 --> 01:04:53,817
Look, I hate to do
this to a friend,

1283
01:04:53,894 --> 01:04:57,125
<i>and I know you're already in
for more than I asked for,</i>

1284
01:04:57,197 --> 01:05:00,634
<i>but I need you to dig
a little deeper.</i>

1285
01:05:02,170 --> 01:05:04,331
<i>I'm right up against it now.</i>

1286
01:05:07,908 --> 01:05:11,105
<i>So, I had
a chance to review
yesterday's tapes.</i>

1287
01:05:11,178 --> 01:05:12,406
And?

1288
01:05:12,479 --> 01:05:16,506
<i>Honestly?
Far too soft, David.</i>

1289
01:05:16,583 --> 01:05:18,676
<i>Go on. Beat me, John.
Beat me with a stick.</i>

1290
01:05:18,752 --> 01:05:21,744
<i>Look. No, I'm serious.</i>

1291
01:05:21,822 --> 01:05:24,223
<i>You have got to make it
more uncomfortable for him.</i>

1292
01:05:24,292 --> 01:05:27,022
<i>You can start by
sitting forward.
You've gotta attack more.</i>

1293
01:05:27,095 --> 01:05:28,687
If he starts
tailing off, bang,

1294
01:05:28,763 --> 01:05:30,161
<i>jump in with
another question.</i>

1295
01:05:30,230 --> 01:05:32,255
<i>Don't trade
generalizations.</i>

1296
01:05:32,332 --> 01:05:33,356
<i>Be specific.</i>

1297
01:05:33,433 --> 01:05:36,528
<i>And above all, don't let
him give these self-serving,
23-minute homilies.</i>

1298
01:05:36,604 --> 01:05:37,628
<i>Right.
And keep your distance</i>

1299
01:05:37,705 --> 01:05:38,967
<i>before the tape
starts running.</i>

1300
01:05:39,040 --> 01:05:40,337
<i>He was toying
with you yesterday.</i>

1301
01:05:40,408 --> 01:05:42,672
<i>All that shit about Ben-Hur
and struggling to raise
the money.</i>

1302
01:05:42,744 --> 01:05:46,805
<i>Those are mind games.
Don't engage.</i>

1303
01:05:46,881 --> 01:05:50,340
<i>Never forget,
you are in there
with a major operator.</i>

1304
01:05:51,587 --> 01:05:52,985
<i>Got it.</i>

1305
01:05:58,192 --> 01:05:59,591
(NIXON CLEARS THROAT)

1306
01:06:00,261 --> 01:06:01,285
<i>Ah.</i>

1307
01:06:02,130 --> 01:06:04,064
The Grand Inquisitor!

1308
01:06:05,233 --> 01:06:07,667
<i>No, just your friendly
neighborhood confidant.</i>

1309
01:06:08,770 --> 01:06:09,896
(GLASS SMASHING)

1310
01:06:12,541 --> 01:06:14,634
<i>It's okay.
We just blew a bulb.</i>

1311
01:06:15,410 --> 01:06:17,901
<i>NIXON: This is why I got
all these Secret Service
guys around.</i>

1312
01:06:17,979 --> 01:06:19,344
<i>There's nothing
to worry about.</i>

1313
01:06:19,414 --> 01:06:22,781
<i>As a president,
you get used to
this kind of stuff.</i>

1314
01:06:22,951 --> 01:06:26,443
<i>DAVIS: Ed, we gotta
get in here and change
out this 750, ASAP.</i>

1315
01:06:31,893 --> 01:06:33,554
<i>(WHISPERING)
Focus, sir.
Yeah.</i>

1316
01:06:36,131 --> 01:06:39,759
<i>Okay, we are back.
Okay, take it
on my count.</i>

1317
01:06:40,601 --> 01:06:43,536
<i>Okay, stand by
to roll tape.
30 seconds.</i>

1318
01:06:43,838 --> 01:06:45,067
<i>DAVIS: Settling.</i>

1319
01:06:45,140 --> 01:06:46,801
You have a pleasant
evening last night?

1320
01:06:46,875 --> 01:06:48,467
<i>Yes, thank you.</i>

1321
01:06:56,618 --> 01:06:58,917
Did you do
any fornicating?

1322
01:06:59,189 --> 01:07:02,214
<i>David, we're starting
with camera two in four,</i>

1323
01:07:02,291 --> 01:07:03,280
(CLEARS THROAT)

1324
01:07:03,359 --> 01:07:05,554
<i>three, two and...</i>

1325
01:07:10,165 --> 01:07:13,396
<i>Mr. President,
you came to office
promising peace,</i>

1326
01:07:13,469 --> 01:07:15,460
but no sooner
did you get into
the White House

1327
01:07:15,537 --> 01:07:19,974
than US involvement
in Vietnam deepened
and the war was prolonged

1328
01:07:20,042 --> 01:07:21,634
<i>with calamitous
consequences.</i>

1329
01:07:21,710 --> 01:07:25,168
<i>Did you feel that you'd
betrayed the people
that had elected you?</i>

1330
01:07:25,247 --> 01:07:29,013
<i>Well, Vietnam
was not my war.</i>

1331
01:07:29,084 --> 01:07:30,745
<i>It was my inheritance.</i>

1332
01:07:30,819 --> 01:07:32,684
<i>And it looked to me...
Jump in.</i>

1333
01:07:32,755 --> 01:07:35,781
<i>...as if the reason
for our being there</i>

1334
01:07:35,858 --> 01:07:40,557
<i>had perhaps not been
adequately understood
by the American people.</i>

1335
01:07:40,963 --> 01:07:42,988
<i>It seemed to me
they hadn't realized</i>

1336
01:07:43,065 --> 01:07:48,264
<i>how important
a test this was
of American credibility.</i>

1337
01:07:48,971 --> 01:07:50,996
The whole world
was watching to see

1338
01:07:51,073 --> 01:07:54,100
<i>if we have the character
to see it through.</i>

1339
01:07:54,177 --> 01:07:56,941
<i>Now, look,
I could have bugged out.
I could have.</i>

1340
01:07:57,013 --> 01:07:59,675
<i>I could have blamed it
on my predecessors.</i>

1341
01:07:59,749 --> 01:08:02,240
I could have
pulled the troops
out of Vietnam early,

1342
01:08:02,318 --> 01:08:04,650
and very possibly,
I would have won

1343
01:08:04,721 --> 01:08:07,951
<i>some Scandinavian peace prize
into the bargain.</i>

1344
01:08:08,023 --> 01:08:09,685
<i>But I believed
in the cause.</i>

1345
01:08:09,759 --> 01:08:15,095
<i>And sometimes, you know,
what you believe in,
it's the harder path.</i>

1346
01:08:15,165 --> 01:08:20,000
<i>You might even say that
I was the last casualty
of the Vietnam War.</i>

1347
01:08:20,070 --> 01:08:22,834
<i>Yeah, tell that
to the paraplegics.</i>

1348
01:08:22,939 --> 01:08:24,270
<i>Come on, David,
Cambodia.</i>

1349
01:08:24,340 --> 01:08:27,503
<i>And Cambodia?
An invasion which everybody
advised you against.</i>

1350
01:08:27,577 --> 01:08:30,602
<i>All the CIA
and Pentagon intelligence
suggested it would fail.</i>

1351
01:08:30,679 --> 01:08:31,771
So why did you do it?

1352
01:08:31,847 --> 01:08:32,906
Well, first of all,

1353
01:08:32,982 --> 01:08:39,410
as a result of
our incursion into Cambodia,
we picked up 22,000 rifles,

1354
01:08:39,489 --> 01:08:43,983
<i>15 million rounds
of ammunition,
150,000 rockets, mortars.</i>

1355
01:08:44,060 --> 01:08:46,290
<i>That's all belonging
to the North Vietnamese,</i>

1356
01:08:46,362 --> 01:08:49,388
which would only otherwise
have been directed

1357
01:08:49,466 --> 01:08:51,593
<i>right onto
American soldiers.</i>

1358
01:08:51,668 --> 01:08:54,932
But one of
the principal justifications
you gave for the incursion

1359
01:08:55,003 --> 01:08:56,665
was the supposed
existence of

1360
01:08:56,739 --> 01:09:01,642
<i>the "headquarters of
the entire Communist military
operation in South Vietnam,"</i>

1361
01:09:01,711 --> 01:09:05,478
<i>a sort of "bamboo Pentagon"
which proved
not to exist at all.</i>

1362
01:09:05,549 --> 01:09:07,210
<i>No, no. Wait a minute
there. No, I was...
And by sending...</i>

1363
01:09:07,284 --> 01:09:10,515
And by sending B-52s
to carpet bomb a country,

1364
01:09:10,588 --> 01:09:13,148
wiping out
whole civilian areas,

1365
01:09:13,224 --> 01:09:16,249
you end up radicalizing
a once moderate people,

1366
01:09:16,326 --> 01:09:18,920
uniting them in
anti-American sentiment

1367
01:09:19,062 --> 01:09:21,657
<i>and creating a monster
in the Khmer Rouge</i>

1368
01:09:21,732 --> 01:09:23,063
<i>that would lead
to civil war...</i>

1369
01:09:23,134 --> 01:09:24,795
<i>All right!
...and genocide.</i>

1370
01:09:24,935 --> 01:09:26,402
<i>Yes, good, good, good.
There it is.</i>

1371
01:09:26,470 --> 01:09:27,630
<i>Okay, run VT.</i>

1372
01:09:27,705 --> 01:09:28,694
<i>Roll tape.</i>

1373
01:10:25,329 --> 01:10:26,557
<i>Well, sir,
I'm sure you'd agree,</i>

1374
01:10:26,630 --> 01:10:28,689
<i>some pretty
stirring images there.</i>

1375
01:10:28,766 --> 01:10:34,535
<i>Look, it was never US policy
to kill civilians.
That's the enemy's way.</i>

1376
01:10:34,606 --> 01:10:35,595
<i>Well, I'm not suggesting...</i>

1377
01:10:35,674 --> 01:10:36,732
<i>And if you're
asking the question</i>

1378
01:10:36,808 --> 01:10:40,904
<i>do I regret the casualties
on both sides in the war,
yeah, sure, of course I do.</i>

1379
01:10:40,979 --> 01:10:43,038
<i>Let me tell you something.
It can just wear you down.</i>

1380
01:10:43,114 --> 01:10:45,048
<i>Well, all right, sir,
when you are faced
with someone who...</i>

1381
01:10:45,116 --> 01:10:47,174
But whenever
I have had my doubts,

1382
01:10:47,251 --> 01:10:49,378
I remembered
the construction worker
in Philadelphia,

1383
01:10:49,453 --> 01:10:50,681
because he came up to me

1384
01:10:50,754 --> 01:10:54,316
<i>and he said, "Sir,
I got only one criticism
of that Cambodia thing.</i>

1385
01:10:54,392 --> 01:10:56,121
<i>"If you'd gone in earlier,</i>

1386
01:10:56,194 --> 01:10:57,957
<i>"you might have
captured the gun</i>

1387
01:10:58,029 --> 01:11:00,054
<i>"that killed my boy
three months ago."</i>

1388
01:11:00,131 --> 01:11:03,123
<i>So you're asking me,
do I regret
going into Cambodia?</i>

1389
01:11:03,201 --> 01:11:05,465
<i>No! I don't.
You know what?</i>

1390
01:11:05,537 --> 01:11:08,597
<i>I wish I'd gone in
sooner and harder.</i>

1391
01:11:08,673 --> 01:11:09,730
<i>SAWYER: Got him.
Safe!</i>

1392
01:11:16,213 --> 01:11:21,084
<i>It was horrifying.
It was horrifying.
And he was so confident.</i>

1393
01:11:21,220 --> 01:11:23,313
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

1394
01:11:24,090 --> 01:11:26,524
REPORTER:
What are you gonna say
about Watergate?

1395
01:11:26,859 --> 01:11:30,158
Sorry, boys,
just all talked out,
you know?

1396
01:11:36,901 --> 01:11:38,300
Better?

1397
01:11:41,907 --> 01:11:44,000
<i>It was.
Unquestionably better.</i>

1398
01:11:49,448 --> 01:11:50,676
<i>What's next?</i>

1399
01:11:51,317 --> 01:11:52,545
<i>Foreign policy.</i>

1400
01:11:55,086 --> 01:12:00,149
<i>Great. Russia, China,
the big power stuff.</i>

1401
01:12:00,225 --> 01:12:02,523
Yeah, so?

1402
01:12:02,594 --> 01:12:04,357
So if he beats him up
like that on Vietnam,

1403
01:12:04,429 --> 01:12:07,331
<i>imagine what he's gonna do
with his real achievements.</i>

1404
01:12:07,400 --> 01:12:08,697
(RESTON LAUGHS)

1405
01:12:09,935 --> 01:12:12,301
<i>It ain't gonna be pretty.</i>

1406
01:12:12,371 --> 01:12:15,101
<i>The answer was
grow by six inches.</i>

1407
01:12:15,174 --> 01:12:18,074
<i>It was agony to watch.</i>

1408
01:12:18,843 --> 01:12:21,744
<i>Now, that's when
Khrushchev called me,
begging me to intervene.</i>

1409
01:12:21,813 --> 01:12:23,838
<i>You see, he and Mao
didn't get along,</i>

1410
01:12:23,915 --> 01:12:26,247
and Khrushchev
knew that the Chairman

1411
01:12:26,318 --> 01:12:28,309
<i>would talk to me,
no one else.</i>

1412
01:12:28,388 --> 01:12:33,155
<i>You see, I was the only one
that Mao would trust
personally, man-to-man.</i>

1413
01:12:33,226 --> 01:12:35,751
When David tried to
lay a finger on him,

1414
01:12:35,829 --> 01:12:38,195
<i>Nixon made mincemeat
out of him.</i>

1415
01:12:39,166 --> 01:12:40,860
<i>ZELNICK:
What "revolution," David?</i>

1416
01:12:40,933 --> 01:12:42,730
You just let
Richard Nixon claim

1417
01:12:42,802 --> 01:12:45,032
the country was in
a state of revolution?

1418
01:12:45,104 --> 01:12:48,369
<i>What, with protestors
"bombing" and "assaulting"
police officers?</i>

1419
01:12:48,441 --> 01:12:49,669
<i>That's not how
I remember it.</i>

1420
01:12:49,742 --> 01:12:52,678
What I remember
is people protesting
peacefully and legitimately

1421
01:12:52,746 --> 01:12:53,906
against the Vietnam War!

1422
01:12:53,980 --> 01:12:55,538
<i>That's what I remember.
Music off, please. Off.</i>

1423
01:12:55,615 --> 01:12:58,311
<i>By the end, wiretapping
students and breaking
into journalists' homes</i>

1424
01:12:58,385 --> 01:13:00,615
<i>was beginning to sound
like a rational response.</i>

1425
01:13:00,687 --> 01:13:02,052
<i>Well, I'm sorry
you feel this way,</i>

1426
01:13:02,122 --> 01:13:04,214
<i>but I simply cannot
share your view.</i>

1427
01:13:04,290 --> 01:13:05,382
About what exactly?

1428
01:13:05,458 --> 01:13:06,823
About any of it, frankly!

1429
01:13:06,892 --> 01:13:09,520
<i>I thought today was
a huge improvement.</i>

1430
01:13:09,595 --> 01:13:10,619
Are you nuts?

1431
01:13:10,696 --> 01:13:12,687
<i>Let me tell you how
bad things were today.</i>

1432
01:13:12,765 --> 01:13:15,792
After the taping finished,
I overheard two members
of the crew say

1433
01:13:15,869 --> 01:13:18,235
they never voted for him
when they had the chance,

1434
01:13:18,305 --> 01:13:21,706
<i>but if he ran
for office again today,
he'd get their support.</i>

1435
01:13:21,775 --> 01:13:24,505
<i>You're making him
look presidential,
for Christ's sake!</i>

1436
01:13:24,578 --> 01:13:27,102
<i>And forget about
the trivia, David.</i>

1437
01:13:27,179 --> 01:13:30,046
Who cares whether Nixon
took the White House bed
to Europe

1438
01:13:30,116 --> 01:13:31,947
when he traveled?
I do!

1439
01:13:32,017 --> 01:13:33,678
<i>Well, it's irrelevant!</i>

1440
01:13:33,753 --> 01:13:37,451
<i>And it's just
the sort of banal anecdote
that would distract a talk...</i>

1441
01:13:38,792 --> 01:13:40,021
A what?

1442
01:13:42,997 --> 01:13:44,897
<i>Go on. No, say it.</i>

1443
01:13:44,966 --> 01:13:47,457
<i>What, you were gonna
say "talk show host"?</i>

1444
01:13:48,802 --> 01:13:51,236
<i>Yeah. Yeah, I was.</i>

1445
01:13:59,079 --> 01:14:03,346
<i>All right, look,
it's useless me trying
to answer your points.</i>

1446
01:14:03,551 --> 01:14:07,487
<i>Frankly, I don't share
any of your sense of
pessimism or alarm.</i>

1447
01:14:09,290 --> 01:14:12,349
And this ridiculous
self-flagellation,

1448
01:14:12,426 --> 01:14:14,894
<i>in my view,
is just depressing.</i>

1449
01:14:15,996 --> 01:14:17,088
No!

1450
01:14:18,965 --> 01:14:23,402
<i>And threatening to derail
the whole enterprise.</i>

1451
01:14:25,071 --> 01:14:30,203
<i>Look. If there is
anyone here who thinks
we're gonna fail,</i>

1452
01:14:31,179 --> 01:14:33,203
they better leave now,

1453
01:14:34,281 --> 01:14:36,511
<i>or it'll infect
everyone else.</i>

1454
01:14:43,557 --> 01:14:44,888
No one?

1455
01:14:48,329 --> 01:14:49,728
<i>Right.</i>

1456
01:14:51,099 --> 01:14:52,225
<i>Good.</i>

1457
01:14:54,703 --> 01:14:58,502
Now, I suggest instead of
festering around the hotel
for the next five days,

1458
01:14:58,573 --> 01:15:01,542
<i>we all go
our separate ways
over Easter.</i>

1459
01:15:03,244 --> 01:15:05,735
But before we go,
Caroline and I
would like you

1460
01:15:05,813 --> 01:15:08,213
to join us for a little
celebratory dinner

1461
01:15:08,282 --> 01:15:11,342
<i>at Patrick Terrail's
new place.</i>

1462
01:15:11,419 --> 01:15:14,184
Celebrate?
Celebrate what, David?

1463
01:15:14,256 --> 01:15:16,019
<i>The fact that we're
all gonna be working
at Burger King?</i>

1464
01:15:16,091 --> 01:15:19,287
<i>What are we celebrating?
It's my birthday, Bob!</i>

1465
01:15:23,965 --> 01:15:29,335
<i>I'd like to
celebrate my birthday
with a few friends.</i>

1466
01:15:35,843 --> 01:15:37,778
(PIANO PLAYING UPBEAT TUNE)

1467
01:15:41,249 --> 01:15:42,511
Look, is that
Neil Diamond?

1468
01:15:42,583 --> 01:15:44,483
<i>(SINGING) Frost and Nixon,
Frost and Nixon</i>

1469
01:15:44,552 --> 01:15:45,883
And is that Sammy Cahn?

1470
01:15:45,953 --> 01:15:47,079
<i>Go together like
Prancer and Vixen</i>

1471
01:15:47,154 --> 01:15:48,519
David,
did you hear that?

1472
01:15:48,589 --> 01:15:50,318
<i>Soaring through the airwaves</i>

1473
01:15:50,391 --> 01:15:52,689
<i>Jesus, that's Hugh Hefner.</i>

1474
01:15:52,760 --> 01:15:53,784
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

1475
01:15:53,861 --> 01:15:55,090
<i>Hoping for several
hefty paydays</i>

1476
01:15:55,163 --> 01:15:56,596
<i>Yeah, I think it is.
With Michael York.</i>

1477
01:15:56,665 --> 01:15:57,962
<i>That's gotta be Bunnies.</i>

1478
01:15:58,033 --> 01:15:59,660
Those are Bunnies?
Those are real Bunnies?

1479
01:15:59,735 --> 01:16:01,135
<i>Frost and Nixon,
Frost and Nixon</i>

1480
01:16:01,204 --> 01:16:02,330
<i>Go together
like Mason and Dixon</i>

1481
01:16:02,405 --> 01:16:05,896
<i>David, just putting it
all together it's the most
extraordinary accomplishment.</i>

1482
01:16:05,974 --> 01:16:07,532
<i>Frost lines up with Dicky...</i>

1483
01:16:07,609 --> 01:16:08,837
<i>No one else
could have done that.</i>

1484
01:16:08,911 --> 01:16:11,641
And these interviews
are always gonna be around
for future generations

1485
01:16:11,713 --> 01:16:14,011
<i>of academics and
political historians.</i>

1486
01:16:14,082 --> 01:16:15,071
That bad?

1487
01:16:15,150 --> 01:16:16,879
<i>He saved it</i>

1488
01:16:16,952 --> 01:16:20,080
<i>He wrote a book
Now here's the hook</i>

1489
01:16:20,155 --> 01:16:21,679
David!

1490
01:16:21,757 --> 01:16:22,781
<i>Patrick.</i>

1491
01:16:22,858 --> 01:16:25,828
<i>He's not a crook
He's paid by David</i>

1492
01:16:26,361 --> 01:16:27,919
(GUESTS APPLAUDING)

1493
01:16:30,465 --> 01:16:32,592
(PLAYING CLASSICAL MUSIC)

1494
01:17:08,071 --> 01:17:12,531
<i>My, what
a festive atmosphere.
Please, don't get up.</i>

1495
01:17:12,609 --> 01:17:16,204
I take it from this
that the interviews
have gone well?

1496
01:17:16,279 --> 01:17:17,940
<i>Better than that, ma'am.
It's a shutout.</i>

1497
01:17:18,014 --> 01:17:20,209
<i>The President's sitting
on an 11-0 lead.</i>

1498
01:17:20,283 --> 01:17:22,308
<i>Really? Well.
Yeah.</i>

1499
01:17:22,385 --> 01:17:24,615
<i>Well, that is
most gratifying.</i>

